      What ethnicity is Tina Fey?
      According to a genealogical DNA test arranged by the television series Finding Your Roots, Fey's ancestry is 94% European, 3% Middle Eastern, and 3% from the Caucasus. She has a brother, Peter, who is eight years older.

      About

      Description

      Elizabeth Stamatina "Tina" Fey is an American actress, comedian, writer, producer, and playwright. Fey was a cast member and head writer for the NBC sketch comedy series Saturday Night Live from 1997 to 2006. Wikipedia
      Born: May 18, 1970 (age 52 years), Upper Darby, Pennsylvania, United States
      Children: Alice Zenobia Richmond, Penelope Athena Richmond
      Spouse: Jeff Richmond (m. 2001)
      Parents: Zenobia Xenakes, Donald Fey
      Production company: Little Stranger
      Height: 1.64 m
